<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,222,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
Species of 
<taxonomicName box="[275,422,223,246]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,422,223,246]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Acentroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reported in association with bromeliads include the following taxa: 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1856" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1856" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basilica">
<emphasis box="[1193,1436,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Acentroptera basilica</emphasis>
Thomson, 1856
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Staines, 2014" authorityName="Staines" authorityYear="2014" box="[349,631,258,283]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata">
<emphasis box="[349,462,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">A. lineata</emphasis>
Staines, 2014
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Uhmann, 1930" authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1930" box="[647,1000,258,283]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevermanni">
<emphasis box="[647,814,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">A. nevermanni</emphasis>
Uhmann, 1930
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Weise, 1910" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1910" box="[1015,1281,258,283]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ohausi">
<emphasis box="[1015,1125,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">A. ohausi</emphasis>
Weise, 1910
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Guerin-Meneville, 1830" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis box="[1296,1436,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">A. pulchella</emphasis>
Guérin-Méneville, 1830
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Baly, 1958" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1958" box="[483,748,294,319]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tessellata">
<emphasis box="[483,620,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">A. tessellata</emphasis>
Baly, 1958
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Albertoni" box="[763,1045,294,319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Albertoni, F. F. &amp; Casari, S. A. (2017) The natural history and morphology of two bromeliad associated hispines from Brazil: Acentroptera basilica Thomson, 1856 and A. cf. tessellata Baly, 1958 (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae: Sceloenoplini). Zootaxa, 4243 (3), 521 - 543. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4243.3.6" type="journal article" year="2017">Albertoni &amp; Casari 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mantovani" box="[1057,1309,294,319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Mantovani, A., Magalhaes, N., Teixeira, M. L., Leitao, G., Staines, C. L. &amp; Resende, B. (2005) First report on host plants and feeding habits of the leaf beetle Acentroptera pulchella Guerin- Meneville (Chrysomelidae, Hispinae). In: Konstantinov, A. S., Penev, L. &amp; Tishechkin, A. (Eds.), First report on host plants and feeding habits of the leaf beetle Acentroptera pulchella Guerin- Meneville (Chrysomelidae, Hispinae). In: Konstantinov, A. S., Penev, L. &amp; Tishechkin, A. (Eds.). Contributions to systematics and biology of insects: Papers celebrating the 80 th birthday of I. K. Lopatin. Pensoft Publishers; Sofia, pp. 153 - 157." type="book chapter" year="2005">
Mantovani 
<emphasis box="[1186,1242,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monros" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Monros, F. &amp; Viana, M. J. (1947) Revision sistematica de los Hispidae Argentinos (Insecta, Coleop. Chrysomeloid.). Anales del Museo Argentino Ciencias Naturales &quot; Bernardino Rivadavia &quot;, 42, 125 - 324." type="journal article" year="1947">Monrós &amp; Viana 1947</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sekerka" box="[315,482,330,355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Sekerka, L. (2014) Review of Imatidiini genera (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 54 (1), 257 - 314." type="journal article" year="2014">Sekerka 2014</bibRefCitation>
; Staines 2014). Adults and larvae of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boheman, 1850)" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[971,1436,330,355]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Spaethiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intricata">
<emphasis box="[971,1212,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Spaethiella intricata</emphasis>
(Boheman, 1850)
</taxonomicName>
(Hemisphaerotini) and adults of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[528,665,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[528,665,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Cephaloleia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1840" box="[725,839,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Imatidiini">Imatidiini</taxonomicName>
) are leaf scrapers of bromeliads in Southern Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="Albertoni" box="[158,396,402,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Albertoni, F. F., Zillikens, A. &amp; Steiner, J. (2016) The associated beetle fauna of Hohenbergia augusta and Uriesea friburgensis (Bromeliaceae) in southern Brazil. Journal of Natural History, 50 (47 - 48), 2917 - 2939. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2016.1218079" type="journal article" year="2016">
Albertoni 
<emphasis box="[274,329,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Uhmann, 1942" authorityName="Uhmann" authorityYear="1942" box="[414,818,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis box="[414,646,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Cephaloleia maxima</emphasis>
Uhmann, 1942
</taxonomicName>
was collected on “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1028,1240,402,427]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Ananas" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrodens">
<emphasis box="[1028,1240,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Ananas macrodens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in Argentina (in quotations because the host species name was apparently misspelled by the collector - Denier - who probably intended 
<taxonomicName authority="E. Morren (Monros &amp; Viana 1947)" authorityName="E. Morren (Monros &amp; Viana" authorityYear="1947" box="[254,891,474,499]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Ananas" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrodontes">
<emphasis box="[254,488,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Ananas macrodontes</emphasis>
É. Morren (
<bibRefCitation author="Monros" box="[625,883,474,499]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Monros, F. &amp; Viana, M. J. (1947) Revision sistematica de los Hispidae Argentinos (Insecta, Coleop. Chrysomeloid.). Anales del Museo Argentino Ciencias Naturales &quot; Bernardino Rivadavia &quot;, 42, 125 - 324." type="journal article" year="1947">Monrós &amp; Viana 1947</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="114" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,222,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName authority="Garcia-Robledo &amp; Staines, 2015 in Garcia-Robledo et al. (2015)" authorityName="Garcia-Robledo &amp; Staines, 2015 in Garcia-Robledo et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[199,1276,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuprewiczae">
<emphasis box="[199,488,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Cephaloleia kuprewiczae</emphasis>
García-Robledo &amp; Staines, 
<quantity box="[829,920,510,535]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1181" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" unit="in" value="2015.0">
2015 
<emphasis box="[898,920,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">in</emphasis>
</quantity>
García-Robledo 
<emphasis box="[1125,1188,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</taxonomicName>
was recently described along with its life cycle and immature stages in association with the bromeliads 
<taxonomicName authority="(Andre) Andre" authorityName="(Andre) Andre" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Pitcairnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arcuata">
<emphasis box="[1225,1436,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Pitcairnia arcuata</emphasis>
(André) André
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mez) Mez (Garcia-Robledo et al. 2015)" authorityName="(Mez) Mez (Garcia-Robledo et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[371,1092,582,607]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Pitcairnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brittoniana">
<emphasis box="[371,618,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Pitcairnia brittoniana</emphasis>
(Mez) Mez (García-Robledo 
<emphasis box="[960,1016,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2015)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1102,1385,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuprewiczae">
<emphasis box="[1102,1385,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Cephaloleia kuprewiczae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from specimens previously identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Garcia-Robledo et al. 2015)" authorityName="Garcia-Robledo et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[739,1353,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrionica">
<emphasis box="[739,1008,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Cephaloleia histrionica</emphasis>
(García-Robledo 
<emphasis box="[1216,1275,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2015)
</taxonomicName>
, which were collected in bromeliads. Given that the specimens collected from bromeliads were subsequently described as 
<emphasis box="[151,339,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Ce. kuprewcizae</emphasis>
, the association of 
<emphasis box="[572,742,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
Ce. 
<taxonomicName box="[621,742,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrionica">histrionica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
with these hosts remains to be confirmed in future natural history assessments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,222,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
A case involving a more intricate misunderstanding is that of 
<bibRefCitation box="[908,1149,762,787]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Burgess, J., Burgess, E. &amp; Lowman, M. (2003) Observations of a beetle herbivore on a bromeliad in Peru. Journal of the Bromeliad Society, 53 (5), 221 - 224." type="journal article">
Burgess 
<emphasis box="[1006,1064,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
, who reported 
<taxonomicName authority="(Oliver, 1808)" authorityName="Oliver" authorityYear="1808" baseAuthorityName="Oliver" baseAuthorityYear="1808" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Calliaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Calliaspis rubra</emphasis>
(Oliver, 1808)
</taxonomicName>
as a bromeliad feeder on 
<taxonomicName authority="L. B. Sm." authorityName="L.B. Sm." box="[668,949,798,823]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nallyi">
<emphasis box="[668,841,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Aechmea nallyi</emphasis>
L.B. Sm.
</taxonomicName>
in Peru. The information was based on two beetle specimens associated with this bromeliad, which were sent to C.L. Staines (USNM) for identification. Staines determined one of the specimens as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oliver" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[648,746,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Calliaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis box="[648,746,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">C. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation box="[808,1044,870,895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Burgess, J., Burgess, E. &amp; Lowman, M. (2003) Observations of a beetle herbivore on a bromeliad in Peru. Journal of the Bromeliad Society, 53 (5), 221 - 224." type="journal article">
Burgess 
<emphasis box="[905,962,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
considered both to be conspecific. A subsequent revision of the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1840" box="[541,651,906,931]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Imatidiini">Imatidiini</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[667,843,906,931]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysomelidae</taxonomicName>
: Cassidinae) (
<bibRefCitation author="Sekerka" box="[999,1157,906,931]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Sekerka, L. (2014) Review of Imatidiini genera (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 54 (1), 257 - 314." type="journal article" year="2014">Sekerka 2014</bibRefCitation>
) listed a specimen at the USNM collection with the following locality data: “Peru: Amazon Center for Education &amp; Environmental Research, 
<date box="[269,394,978,1003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" value="1999-03-28">28.iii.1999</date>
, M. Lowman &amp; D. Krabill lgt.” The identification label on this exemplar confirmed that it had been determined by Staines as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[579,702,1014,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Spaethiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erhardti">
<emphasis box="[579,702,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">S. erhardti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 2000. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sekerka" box="[826,1004,1014,1039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Sekerka, L. (2014) Review of Imatidiini genera (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 54 (1), 257 - 314." type="journal article" year="2014">Sekerka (2014)</bibRefCitation>
then suggested that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1255,1379,1014,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Spaethiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erhardti">
<emphasis box="[1255,1379,1014,1039]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">S. erhardti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[330,425,1050,1075]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Aechmea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nallyi">
<emphasis box="[330,425,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">A. nallyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oliver" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[549,646,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Calliaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis box="[549,646,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">C. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<bibRefCitation box="[684,919,1050,1075]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Burgess, J., Burgess, E. &amp; Lowman, M. (2003) Observations of a beetle herbivore on a bromeliad in Peru. Journal of the Bromeliad Society, 53 (5), 221 - 224." type="journal article">
Burgess 
<emphasis box="[780,837,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
had reported. This is substantiated by the fact that the illustrations of the adults presented by 
<bibRefCitation box="[676,911,1086,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Burgess, J., Burgess, E. &amp; Lowman, M. (2003) Observations of a beetle herbivore on a bromeliad in Peru. Journal of the Bromeliad Society, 53 (5), 221 - 224." type="journal article">
Burgess 
<emphasis box="[773,829,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
correspond to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1078,1196,1086,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Spaethiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erhardti">
<emphasis box="[1078,1196,1086,1111]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">S. erhardti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on a personal correspondence with M. Lowman, it seems clear that 
<bibRefCitation box="[766,1006,1122,1147]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Burgess, J., Burgess, E. &amp; Lowman, M. (2003) Observations of a beetle herbivore on a bromeliad in Peru. Journal of the Bromeliad Society, 53 (5), 221 - 224." type="journal article">
Burgess 
<emphasis box="[864,922,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
dealt with two species both of which were correctly identified by the same specialist. For this reason, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oliver" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[887,986,1158,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Calliaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis box="[887,986,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">C. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1043,1169,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1043,1165,1158,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Spaethiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erhardti">S. erhardti</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
are here treated as leaf scrapers of bromeliads in Peru. These species are not known to be leaf miners as immatures or adults. Alternatively, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sekerka" box="[151,323,1230,1255]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Sekerka, L. (2014) Review of Imatidiini genera (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 54 (1), 257 - 314." type="journal article" year="2014">Sekerka (2014)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that the largest injuries shown in 
<figureCitation box="[824,933,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1868,1890]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1847]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 25. Calliaspis umbonata Hincks, 1956 mature larva. (16) Clypeus and labrum; (17) epipharynx; (18, 19) lateral outlines of labrum and epipharynx in frontal view; (20) scale-like projections of epipharynx; (21) maxilla and labium, ventral view; (22) maxilla and hypopharynx, dorsal view; (23, 24, 25) mandible: (23) dorso-external view; (24) ventro-internal view; (25) external view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/852116/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Figure 16</figureCitation>
(p. 222) of 
<bibRefCitation box="[1069,1305,1230,1255]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refString="Burgess, J., Burgess, E. &amp; Lowman, M. (2003) Observations of a beetle herbivore on a bromeliad in Peru. Journal of the Bromeliad Society, 53 (5), 221 - 224." type="journal article">
Burgess 
<emphasis box="[1166,1223,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
could have been caused by an 
<taxonomicName box="[362,509,1267,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acentroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[362,509,1267,1290]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Acentroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, instead of adults of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1836" box="[832,946,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Calliaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[832,946,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Calliaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Barber et Bridwell, 1940" authorityName="Barber et Bridwell" authorityYear="1940" box="[982,1398,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Spaethiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[982,1108,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Spaethiella</emphasis>
Barber et Bridwell, 1940
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
